  "prompt": "What is required to own a Rolls Royce?",
  "response": "To own a Rolls-Royce, several key requirements and considerations include:\n\n1. Financial Capacity\n- High purchase price (typically $300,000 to $500,000+)\n- Luxury models can cost over $1 million\n- Significant ongoing maintenance costs\n\n2. Financial Qualifications\n- Excellent credit score\n- Substantial annual income\n- Ability to afford insurance and maintenance\n\n3. Legal Requirements\n- Valid driver's license\n- Proof of insurance\n- Vehicle registration\n- Meeting local vehicle regulations\n\n4. Practical Considerations\n- Specialized maintenance and servicing\n- Access to authorized Rolls-Royce service centers\n- Higher fuel and maintenance expenses\n- Potentially higher insurance premiums\n\n5. Personal Factors\n- Appreciation for luxury and craftsmanship\n- Understanding of the brand's heritage\n- Desire for a prestigious vehicle\n\n6. Purchase Options\n- Direct purchase from authorized dealerships\n- Custom ordering\n- Pre-owned vehicles from certified dealers\n\n7. Additional Recommendations\n- Financial stability\n- Understanding of luxury car ownership\n- Willingness to invest in premium maintenance\n\nOwnership requires significant financial resources and commitment to maintaining a high-end luxury vehicle.",
